-- Italy Regulator Sets Unbundling Fees for Access to Telecom Italia's Grid
-- B y   C h i a r a   R e m o n d i n i
-- 2010-11-11T14:04:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-11/italy-regulator-sets-unbundling-fees-for-access-to-telecom-italia-s-grid.html
Italy’s communications regulator,
Agcom, approved the unbundling fees that rivals have to pay
Telecom Italia SpA to access its fixed-line network, it
said in an e-mailed statement today.  The unbundling tariffs will be increased to 8.70 euros a
month in 2010, 9.02 euros a month in 2011 and 9.28 euros a month
in 2012, it said. FastWeb SpA, Tiscali SpA and Vodafone Plc said
in a statement that they were “disappointed” with the fees.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chiara Remondini at 
 cremondini@bloomberg.net  